  "prompt": "How should I handle my co workers that purposely ignore my texts?",
  "response": "Here are some professional approaches to handle this situation:\n\n1. Direct communication\n- Ask them in person why they're not responding\n- Be polite and non-confrontational\n- Seek to understand if there's a reason for their lack of response\n\n2. Verify communication methods\n- Confirm they received your texts\n- Check if they prefer email or another communication channel\n- Ensure your messages are clear and necessary\n\n3. Professional Follow-up\n- Send a follow-up email documenting your attempt to communicate\n- Copy relevant team members or supervisors if needed\n- Keep documentation of communication attempts\n\n4. Assess work impact\n- Determine if their non-responsiveness affects your work\n- If it's hampering productivity, discuss with your supervisor\n- Focus on how their lack of communication impacts team performance\n\n5. Consider underlying issues\n- They might be overwhelmed\n- There could be personal or professional challenges\n- Be empathetic and understanding\n\n6. Formal channels\n- If persistent, discuss with HR or your manager\n- Present specific examples and potential work disruptions\n- Seek mediation or resolution\n\n7. Stay professional\n- Maintain a calm and courteous demeanor\n- Don't take it personally\n- Focus on work objectives\n\nRemember, the goal is maintaining professional communication and workplace effectiveness.",
